AB  - Susan Blackmore's book, The Meme Machine, was considered, by Dawkins, as the one that takes Memetics further. In this book, Blackmore depicts many Memetics analysis of several phenomena as long as trying to solve some of the most fundamental questions within this area and also present some of the most used definitions of the main concepts of Memetics. As important as the book might be, Blackmore makes the mistake of ignoring the researches that could support her analysis and, in this way, she creates interesting narratives, but without an empirical foundation.
