AB  - Memetics is a new theory of cultural evolution and transmission based on neo-Darwinism by Chesterman. This paper discusses the relationship between memes and translation, probes into translation strategies from the point of the memes types and evolution, and looks particularly at the strategies of domesticating and foreignizing translation in the hope of reproduction and innovation for the meme transmission. As it highlights the importance of translation memes in the process of translation, this paper finally attempts to draw out memetics of translation theory and provides a new perspective on how to better convey cross-cultural communication.
