AB  - This study explored L2 writing development by focusing on one of the linguistic features of texts (accuracy) from a linguistic memetics perspective, investigating whether two groups of university students would form a sharp contrast in their EFL writing accuracy through a school year of timed writing task. The experimental group adopted listening & speaking-to-write approach designed against the principles of linguistic memetics, whereas the control group employed the traditional writing approach. Results indicate that the two groups demonstrated statistically significant difference in their writing accuracy. This study, therefore, suggests that listening & speaking-to-write approach based on linguistic memetics should be conducive to L2 writing to some degree.
