AB  - Memetics is a newly developed theory introduced by the biologist of Oxford Richard Dawkins in 1976. It is used to explain the relations between things and the law of inheritance of cultural evolutional form the point of horizontal and vertical view. The core concept of Memetics is "meme" which generates from "gene". And the concept of meme is imitation. Meme is copied and spread through imitation. Therefore anything can be called meme if it is copied and spread by imitation, for example, language. This paper tries to analyze the Chinese internet language with memetics. Through classifying the internet language and summarizing the features of internet language, the author attempt to get some laws of the internet language spread to promote the study of language meme.
