AB  - New English-Chinese translators often make mistakes while translating the legal documents, because many words used in legal texts have both ordinary meanings and technical meanings. Based on the parallel English-Chinese legal documents, this paper explores the translation strategies for common words with legal meanings. From the perspective of memetics, words, sentences and passages are all memes, they can be transmitted from culture to culture. So, it is suggested that the sample sentences containing the common words with legal meanings and their translation be learned first, which will eventually help improve the quality of Chinese translation.
