AB  - Writing is a dynamic process, involving a series of cognitive activities of the writers. In teaching, the development of learners' ability to compose is a major target. To achieve this end, teaching always starts with the improvement of students' ability to imitate the target language. As a practical attempt, the Length Approach was presented by Professor Wang Churning at the dawn of this century. Memetics was introduced into English education by Professor He Ziran roughly during this same period. In this paper, these two ideas are combined with each other, with the emphasis on accumulation and the use of "memes" to enrich language materials and to build context for "write-to-learn".
