AB  - Human cognition has been simulated with artificial intelligence because it's very useful to solve problems; however, the cognitive processes also cause some difficulties to individual and society. The results of the proposed model in this paper are part of an investigation aimed to study such difficulties, using artificial social agents with moral development at competitive environments where selfishness and altruism are decisive. In this regard, memetics provides evolutionary terminology to explain the cultural development of beliefs, artifacts and behaviors, in an egotists and altruists community capable to assimilate, to innovate and to exchange ideas, to get individual and group benefits through dialectical or behavioral competitions. As that development could be simulated to model the replicative process of certain cerebral elements, called neuro-memes, this paper presents an agent able to replicate the behavior of other agent, using an artificial neural network with unsupervised and supervised learning.
