AB  - This research is located at the border of the areas of Communication, memetics and imaginary studies. We have as presupposition the existence of a communicational imaginary, in which the contemporary man is ruled by his abilities in social networks, by the demand of the publicity of the private, the obsessiveness of the sharing of the intimacy and the exorbitant amount of images. Considering memes as a significant phenomenon of this communicational imaginary, we seek to understand the dynamics and path of memes in the midst of this plethora of images. From the concept of iconophagy, we deal with the exacerbated multiplication of the images and the path of memes starting from a marginalized environment until it is integrated to the social roles and to a rational level of thought. Thus, it is the general objective of this research to understand the dynamics and the path of memes amidst the plethora of images in the context of communicational imagery and to investigate the multiplication of memes as representative of the myriad images in contemporary imagery.
